    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-02-12T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-02-12T18:00:00-05:00" n="732"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d732">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Korea/2–448: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Political Adviser in Korea</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jacobs</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-02-12T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 12, 1948—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>35. As you are aware we may at a later stage desire to take up again Soviet offer
                    of mutual withdrawal of occupation forces. We assume that you will therefore
                    through Mitchell or other appropriate channels consider advisability of discreet
                    action to counteract such false statements as that referred to in last sentence
                        <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 47 Feb 4<note n="1" xml:id="d732fn1"
                        >Not printed.</note> that simultaneous troop withdrawal offer “was turned
                    down”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
